<item>
            <title>[LU-268] Possible bug in userspace block handling when enabling MPP </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-268</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>
&lt;p&gt;When choosing a block for multiple mount protection near the end of the file system it can fail.  There is a patch that changes mmp_blk to (long long)mmp_blk  which should prevent the MMP block from overwriting block filesystem data.  A patch has been provided but it has not been inspected from bug24209 mmp_blk64.patch.  We would like this patch to be evaluated.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are concerned if we have current customers who have full filesystems and enable MPP they could be putting data at risk.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
